# Project Context

[One-line description of the capstone project — e.g. "AI tool that quizzes engineers on a codebase and generates gap-focused documentation."]

## Stack

- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Backend/logic: Node.js
- AI: Claude API
- Package manager: npm

## Conventions

- Functional components only, no class components
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, use `unknown` + type guards
- Named exports only, no default exports
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`)
- Run `npm run lint` before committing

## Architecture Notes

- Keep AI-analysis logic (repo parsing, decision-map extraction) separate from UI components
- API keys and secrets go in `.env`, never committed — check `.gitignore` before adding new env vars
